messages.message: Hey. We have some logistics documents for a prospect, which are often carbon copies so the writing is slightly faded depending on how "motivated" was the writer . I would expect the OCR to adjust the contrast if necessary. Attached is an example. Supplier Vendor and Purchase Order are extracted, but not Original Document and Date. Any advice ?
@Hari / @Balaram I know we do some pre-processing, but I'm not sure if we do any contrast adjustment?
AFAIK, we don't do contrast adjustment. @Gaurav Saini can you confirm?
Yeah, we don't do it. @cyrille it would be helpful to post and check with solution-eng(<#CKBRX13L5|>). They would have done it via custom functions for a use case.
